'''Jukka Antero Hienonen''' (born August 9, 1961) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[businessman]]. He has resigned from the position of President & CEO at [[Finnair|Finnair Plc]] August 7, 2009 (effective Jan 31st, 2010).<ref>[http://www.finnairgroup.com/group/group_11_1_1.html?&Id=hex_200908070000404593.html Finnair press release]</ref><ref name="urlHelsingin Sanomat - International Edition - Business & Finance">{{cite web |url=http://www.hs.fi/english/article/New+Finnair+CEO+Jukka+Hienonen+gets+his+wings/1135218198008 |title=Helsingin Sanomat - International Edition - Business & Finance |format= |work= |accessdate=2010-11-06}}</ref> His previous positions include [[Vice President]] at [[Stockmann]]. Hienonen lives in the city of [[Kauniainen]] with his wife and two daughters. He is fluent in [[Finnish language|Finnish]], [[English language|English]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]] and [[Russian language|Russian]].

