{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Wim van der Leegte | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Wilhelmus Gerardus Stephanus Maria van der Leegte | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1947|08}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Dutch | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = [[Eindhoven]], Netherlands | education = | alma mater = | occupation = | title = Former president, [[VDL Groep]] | term = 1966-2016 | predecessor = | successor = | known for = | boards = | salary = | networth = US$1.5 billion (February 2017)<ref name="Forbes" /> | spouse = married | parents = [[Pieter van der Leegte]] | children = 3 | relations = | website = }}
'''Wilhelmus Gerardus Stephanus Maria "Wim" van der Leegte''' (born August 1947)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/iQooF-CS6x4U7K6rGqsudswcGvU/appointments |title=Wilhelmus Gerardus Stephanus Maria VAN DER LEEGTE - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House) |publisher=Beta.companieshouse.gov.uk |date=12 March 1992 |accessdate=13 February 2017}}</ref> is a Dutch [[billionaire]], and runs the Netherlands-based [[VDL Groep]].<ref name="Forbes">{{cite web|title=The World's Billionaires: Wim Van Der Leegte|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/wim-van-der-leegte/|website=Forbes|accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref>
==Career== VDL Groep, one of Europe's largest privately-held car and bus makers, was founded in 1953 by his father [[Pieter van der Leegte]], when it started making parts for trucking companies.<ref name="Forbes" />
In January 2016 VDL announced that van der Leegte would be step down in November, after 50 years as president.
==Personal life== Van der Leegte is married with three children and lives in [[Eindhoven]], Netherlands.<ref name="Forbes" /> His three children: Pieter, Jennifer and Willem, are all members of the executive board, and own shares in the company.
